  "prompt": "Which are the top 5 Bollywood songs of 2015?",
  "response": "In 2015, several Bollywood songs gained immense popularity and topped the charts. Here are five of the standout tracks from that year:\n\n1. **\"Gerua\"** - From the movie *Dilwale*, sung by Arijit Singh and Antara Mitra, this romantic track featured the iconic pairing of Shah Rukh Khan and Kajol.\n\n2. **\"Prem Ratan Dhan Payo\"** - The title track of the movie of the same name, sung by Arijit Singh, became very popular and was associated with the film's festive themes.\n\n3. **\"Bhula Dunga\"** - A romantic track from the film *Baaghi*, sung by Arijit Singh, captured the hearts of listeners with its soulful melody.\n\n4. **\"Sunny Sunny\"** - Featured in the movie *Yaariyan*, this upbeat and catchy number sung by Yo Yo Honey Singh and Neha Kakkar became a party anthem.\n\n5. **\"Ae Mere Humsafar\"** - From the film *Baazigar*, this romantic song sung by Vinod Rathod was celebrated for its melodious tune and poignant lyrics.\n\nThese songs not only topped the charts but also became integral to the soundscape of Bollywood in 2015.",
